HEADWORD: Stereochromy
<hw>Ste`re*och"ro*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Stereo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>chrw^ma</grk> color.]</ety> <def>A
style of painting on plastered walls or stone, in which the colors are
rendered permanent by sprinklings of water, in which is mixed a
proportion of soluble glass (a silicate of soda).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stereoelectric</ent>⟦br⟧
